TNK-BP’s Incoming Chief Urges Independent Management, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-03T20:35:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-03/tnk-bp-s-incoming-chief-urges-independent-management-ft-reports.html
TNK-BP Deputy Chief Executive Officer
Maxim Barsky, who was scheduled to take over as chief executive
officer in January, has called on the oil venture between  BP Plc (BP/) 
and a group of Russian billionaires to introduce independent
management or risk damaging the company’s international growth
plans, the Financial Times reported, citing an interview with
Barsky in  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 